data.title: Katherine R. Dollar on LinkedIn: Ranger said it was a good day to film some new content for our LinkedIn…
data.meta_description:
Ranger said it was a good day to film some new content for our LinkedIn friends because it’s a fall, rainy and cozy day. 

So stay tuned!
data.text:
In the world of branded content, we often get caught up in showcasing our product's features and benefits. But what if I told you that addressing the problem can be even more effective? Take the classic Hutch ad by Nirvana Films, for instance. They didn't just boast about their network coverage; they tackled the prevalent issue of network problems head-on. And the most beautiful thing about this ad is that despite knowing it is an advertisement, we tend to watch it all the way to the end. In my opinion, this approach is genius. Why? Because it engages the audience on a deeper level. It's relatable. It says, "We understand your pain, and we have a solution. Link to the ad: https://lnkd.in/g7N6dzHA

Create your entire product launch campaign in a single prompt. You released a feature, you're super stoked, now it's time to tell the world about it. You create a walkthrough video, but now you have to turn all those juicy details into content across a bunch of different platforms. But with GoCharlie.ai you can do it in a single prompt. Try it out for yourself, using the prompt template below. "Use this https://lnkd.in/ggeSx9sq to write a blog about the new feature update, an email to go to our customers, 3 instagram captions advertising the features, and a post for our customer community on facebook structured like a step by step guide"
